criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  type 2 diabetic subjects

          -  age between 50 and 75 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  glycosylated hemoglobin (HbA1c) less than 7% or more than 10%;

          -  triglyceride more than 4.5 mmol/L;

          -  current insulin treatment;

          -  change of the medications for anti-diabetes, hypertension, hyperlipidemia and
             anti-platelet in recent four weeks;

          -  abnormal renal function (serum creatinine > 177 Î¼mol/L;

          -  abnormal liver function test results (more than two-fold upper limit of normal range);

          -  severe systemic disease such as immune disorder, cancer, acute or chronic inflammation
             disease;

          -  smoking in recent 1 year;

          -  alcoholism (more than two drinks daily);

          -  using steroid or drugs with unknown components;

          -  pregnancy or breast-feeding.
